Class uk.ac.ebi.pride.utilities.data.core.IonType extends CvParam implements Serializable

Serialized Fields

charge

int charge
The charge of the identified fragmentation ions.

index

java.util.List<E> index
The index of ions identified as integers, following standard notation for a-c, x-z e.g. if b3 b5 and b6 have been identified, the index would store "3 5 6". For internal ions, the index contains pairs defining the start and end point - see specification document for examples. For immonium ions, the index is the position of the identified ion within the peptide sequence - if the peptide contains the same amino acid in multiple positions that cannot be distinguished, all positions should be given.

measures

java.util.Map<K,V> measures
An array of values for a given type of measure and for a particular ion type, in parallel to the index of ions identified.

Serialized Fields

avgMassDelta

java.util.List<E> avgMassDelta
In the new validation approach for pride modification objects, just one Average Mass Delta could be associated to a Modification. In the MzIdentMl Modification object only one Average Mass Delta is annotated.

location

int location
Location of the modification within the peptide - position in peptide sequence, counted from the N-terminus residue, starting at position 1. Specific modifications to the N-terminus should be given the location 0. Modification to the C-terminus should be given as peptide length + 1. MzIdentMl and PrideXML

modDatabase

java.lang.String modDatabase
modification database where accession is from (used for PRIDE Objects)

modDatabaseVersion

java.lang.String modDatabaseVersion
modification database version is (used for PRIDE Objects)

monoisotopicMassDelta

java.util.List<E> monoisotopicMassDelta
In the new validation approach for pride modification objects, just one MonoIsotopic Mass Delta could be associated to a Modification. In the MzIdentMl Modification object only one MonoIsotopic Mass Delta is annotated.

residues

java.util.List<E> residues
Possible Residues for this modification. In the PRIDE Object this attribute do not exist but in the pride modification validator One modification can be related with more than one specificity. In MzIdentML Object the Modification is related with more than one specificity.

DBSequence dbSequence
A reference to the protein sequence in which the specified peptide has been linked.

endPosition

java.lang.Integer endPosition
The index position of the last amino acid of the peptide inside the protein sequence, where the first amino acid of the protein sequence is position 1. Must be provided unless this is a de novo search.

frame

java.lang.Integer frame
The translation frame of this sequence if this is PeptideEvidence derived from nucleic acid sequence.

peptideSequence

PeptideSequence peptideSequence
A reference to the identified (poly)peptide sequence in the Peptide element.

postResidue

char postResidue
Post flanking residue. If the peptide is C-terminal, post="-" and not post="". If for any reason it is unknown (e.g. denovo), post="?" should be used.

preResidue

char preResidue
Previous flanking residue. If the peptide is N-terminal, pre="-" and not pre="". If for any reason it is unknown (e.g. denovo), pre="?" should be used.

startPosition

java.lang.Integer startPosition
Start position of the peptide inside the protein sequence, where the first amino acid of the protein sequence is position 1. Must be provided unless this is a de novo search.

translationTable

IdentifiableParamGroup translationTable
The details specifying this translation table are captured as cvParams, e.g. translation table, translation start codons and translation table description (see specification document and mapping file)

decoy

Set to true if the peptide is matched to a decoy sequence.

calculatedMassToCharge

double calculatedMassToCharge

The calculated isoelectric point of the (poly)peptide, with relevant modifications included. Do not supply this value if the PI cannot be calculated properly.

chargeState

int chargeState
The charge state of the identified peptide.

experimentalMassToCharge

double experimentalMassToCharge
The mass-to-charge value measured in the experiment in Daltons / charge.

fragmentation

java.util.List<E> fragmentation
The product ions identified in this result.

massTable

MassTable massTable
A reference should be given to the MassTable used to calculate the sequenceMass only if more than one MassTable has been given.

peptideEvidenceList

java.util.List<E> peptideEvidenceList
Reference to the PeptideEvidence element identified. If a specific sequence can be assigned to multiple proteins and or positions in a protein all possible PeptideEvidence elements should be referenced here.

score

Score score
Score stores a number of peptide scores for a list of search engines.

peptideSequence

PeptideSequence peptideSequence
A reference to the identified (poly)peptide sequence in the Peptide element.

rank

int rank
For an MS/MS result set, this is the rank of the identification quality as scored by the search engine. 1 is the top rank. If multiple identifications have the same top score, they should all be assigned rank =1. For PMF data, the rank attribute may be meaningless and values of rank = 0 should be given.

passThreshold

boolean passThreshold
Set to true if the producers of the file has deemed that the identification has passed a given threshold or been validated as correct. If no such threshold has been set, value of true should be given for all results.

sample

Sample sample
A reference should be provided to link the SpectrumIdentificationItem to a Sample if more than one sample has been described in the AnalysisSampleCollection.

spectraData

SpectraData spectraData
A reference to a spectra data set (e.g. a spectra file).

spectrum

Spectrum spectrum
The locally unique id for the spectrum in the spectra data set specified by SpectraData_ref. External guidelines are provided on the use of consistent identifiers for spectra in different external formats.

retentionTime

java.lang.String retentionTime
Add retention time to the SpectrumIdentification Item.
